{
  "stem": "10588.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they went to the rabbi.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the rabbi-- it was a community within a community.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Double taxes you would pay, taxes for charity, for holding up the Jewish institutions, and charity government.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the [BACKGROUND NOISE] Jewish community was like self-contained.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So anyhow-- so I remember that the story was that two men came for [NON-ENGLISH] That means, for the rabbi to settle dispute.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He listened to both.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he said, my son, you are right to the first one.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then he listened to [INAUDIBLE] and said, you are right.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the-- rabbi's wife standing there listening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "She said, my dear husband, how can both be right when they both disagree?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He said, my wife, you are right, too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Which means to tell that from their point of view, everybody's right.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So the fact that I grew up in a home where Yiddish songs, Yiddish literature, Yiddish sayings, proverbs was quoted constantly.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So in fact, I remember my grandmother had so many Yiddish proverbs and so many folk songs and everything else.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "What I love, my grandmother love, I loved the wonderful-- she was a wonderful woman.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And she loved me unconditionally, so did my parents.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But what I loved the foremost is that she never took me for granted.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whenever-- whenever she asked me to do a little errand for her and I went, she would thank me many, many times and bless me.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Says, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I said, grandmother, it's just a little thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my grandmother used to answer with a smile.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Yes, my child.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But kindness and caring are not just little things.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So it's the values that were expressed in the song and in the literature and everything.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This is what nourished me spiritually.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
